chemoreception.notes: As polychaetes, Onuphidae likely rely on chemoreception for detecting food and mates. This is a general trait for marine worms.

mechanoreception.notes: As polychaetes, Onuphidae likely rely on mechanoreception for sensing their environment and detecting vibrations. This is a general trait for marine worms.
